<!DOCTYPE html><html lang="en"><head>  <meta charset="UTF-8" />  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />  <title>Gemini - Master English Confidently</title>  <style>    /* Reset and base */    * {      box-sizing: border-box;      margin: 0;      padding: 0;      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;    }    body {      background-color: #fff; /* White interface */      color: #333;      line-height: 1.6;      padding: 20px;      min-height: 100vh;      display: flex;      flex-direction: column;    }    header {      text-align: center;      margin-bottom: 40px;      border-bottom: 2px solid #ddd;      padding-bottom: 10px;    }    header h1 {      font-weight: 700;      color: #1a237e; /* Deep blue */      margin-bottom: 8px;      font-size: 2.5rem;    }    header p {      font-size: 1.2rem;      font-style: italic;      color: #555;    }    nav {      display: flex;      justify-content: center;      gap: 25px;      margin-bottom: 30px;      font-weight: 600;    }    nav a {      text-decoration: none;      color: #1a237e;      padding: 8px 15px;      border-radius: 25px;      transition: background-color 0.3s ease;      cursor: pointer;    }    nav a:hover,    nav a.active {      background-color: #1a237e;      color: #fff;    }    main {      flex-grow: 1;      max-width: 900px;      margin: 0 auto;    }    section {      margin-bottom: 50px;      display: none;    }    section.active {      display: block;    }    h2 {      color: #303f9f;      margin-bottom: 15px;      border-left: 6px solid #3f51b5;      padding-left: 12px;    }    article {      margin-bottom: 20px;    }    article p {      margin-bottom: 12px;      font-size: 1.1rem;    }    .exercise {      background-color: #eef1fb;      border-left: 4px solid #3f51b5;      padding: 15px 20px;      margin-top: 10px;      border-radius: 5px;    }    button {      background-color: #1a237e;      color: white;      border: none;      padding: 10px 18px;      font-size: 1rem;      border-radius: 6px;      cursor: pointer;      transition: background-color 0.3s ease;      margin-top: 10px;    }    button:hover {      background-color: #3949ab;    }    footer {      text-align: center;      font-size: 0.9rem;      color: #999;      margin-top: 40px;      padding-top: 10px;      border-top: 1px solid #ddd;    }    /* Responsive */    @media (max-width: 600px) {      nav {        flex-direction: column;        gap: 15px;      }    }  </style></head><body>  <header>    <h1>Gemini</h1>    <p>Master English Confidently - Learn, Practice, and Speak Fluent English</p>  </header>
  <nav>    <a href="#confidence" class="active">Confidence Building</a>    <a href="#phrases">Powerful Phrases</a>    <a href="#pronunciation">Pronunciation</a>    <a href="#conversation">Real Conversations</a>  </nav>
  <main>    <section id="confidence" class="active">      <h2>Building Confidence in English Speaking</h2>      <article>        <p>To speak English confidently, start by embracing mistakes as part of learning. Practice consistently and focus on expressing your ideas rather than perfection.</p>        <p>Try daily affirmations like: <em>"I can improve my English every day."</em></p>        <div class="exercise">          <strong>Exercise:</strong> Record yourself speaking about your day for 2 minutes. Listen and note areas to improve, but celebrate progress.        </div>      </article>    </section>
    <section id="phrases">      <h2>Powerful English Phrases for Everyday Use</h2>      <article>        <p>Learn a core set of impactful phrases to sound natural and confident. Using these phrases in daily conversation will boost your fluency.</p>        <ul>          <li>"Could you please repeat that?"</li>          <li>"I see what you mean."</li>          <li>"That's an interesting point."</li>          <li>"Let me think about that."</li>          <li>"How do you feel about...?"</li>        </ul>        <div class="exercise">          <strong>Exercise:</strong> Practice using these phrases in sentences aloud. Try to use at least three phrases in a conversation today.        </div>      </article>    </section>
    <section id="pronunciation">      <h2>Mastering Pronunciation</h2>      <article>        <p>Clear pronunciation builds confidence and helps others understand you better. Focus on the sounds and rhythm of English.</p>        <p>Use online tools or apps to hear native pronunciation and mimic the sounds.</p>        <div class="exercise">          <strong>Exercise:</strong> Choose 5 tricky words (e.g., "comfortable," "schedule," "though") and practice pronouncing them slowly, then naturally.        </div>      </article>    </section>
    <section id="conversation">      <h2>Real Conversations Practice</h2>      <article>        <p>Engage in practical conversation scenarios that you might encounter in daily life or work. This prepares you to respond confidently in real time.</p>        <p>Example scenario: Ordering food</p>        <div class="exercise">          <strong>Exercise:</strong> Role-play ordering at a restaurant. Practice both ordering and asking polite questions like "What do you recommend?" or "Is this dish spicy?"        </div>      </article>    </section>  </main>
  <footer>    &copy; 2024 Gemini English Learning. All rights reserved.  </footer>
  <script>    // Navigation interaction    const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('nav a');    const sections = document.querySelectorAll('main section');
    navLinks.forEach(link => {      link.addEventListener('click', e => {        e.preventDefault();        const targetId = link.getAttribute('href').substring(1);
        // Remove active class from all nav links and sections        navLinks.forEach(nav => nav.classList.remove('active'));        sections.forEach(sec => sec.classList.remove('active'));
        // Add active class to clicked link and target section        link.classList.add('active');        document.getElementById(targetId).classList.add('active');      });    });  </script></body></html>
